{"parse":{"title":"Pointer (rod)","pageid":5933040,"revid":832632665,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\">For the electronic counterpart, see <a href=\"/wiki/Laser_pointer\" title=\"Laser pointer\">Laser pointer</a>. For a computer input device with the same name, see <a href=\"/wiki/Pointing_stick\" title=\"Pointing stick\">Pointing stick</a>.</div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Robert_McNamera_pointing_to_a_map_of_Vietnam_at_a_press_conference,_1965.JPG\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7e/Robert_McNamera_pointing_to_a_map_of_Vietnam_at_a_press_conference%2C_1965.JPG/220px-Robert_McNamera_pointing_to_a_map_of_Vietnam_at_a_press_conference%2C_1965.JPG\" width=\"220\" height=\"146\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7e/Robert_McNamera_pointing_to_a_map_of_Vietnam_at_a_press_conference%2C_1965.JPG/330px-Robert_McNamera_pointing_to_a_map_of_Vietnam_at_a_press_conference%2C_1965.JPG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7e/Robert_McNamera_pointing_to_a_map_of_Vietnam_at_a_press_conference%2C_1965.JPG/440px-Robert_McNamera_pointing_to_a_map_of_Vietnam_at_a_press_conference%2C_1965.JPG 2x\" data-file-width=\"3648\" data-file-height=\"2416\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Robert_McNamera_pointing_to_a_map_of_Vietnam_at_a_press_conference,_1965.JPG\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/wiki/Robert_McNamara\" title=\"Robert McNamara\">Robert McNamara</a> points at a <a href=\"/wiki/Vietnam\" title=\"Vietnam\">Vietnam</a> map using a pointing stick.</div></div></div>\n<p>A <b>pointer</b> or <b>pointing stick</b> is a solid rod used to point manually, in the form of a stick, but always finished off or artificially produced.\n</p><p>The typical pointer is simply a long, slender, often flexible stick made in a strong material, designed to indicate places on <a href=\"/wiki/Maps\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Maps\">maps</a>, words on <a href=\"/wiki/Blackboard\" title=\"Blackboard\">blackboards</a> etc.<sup id=\"cite_ref-dictcom_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-dictcom-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-uiuc_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-uiuc-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\nIn addition it may be used like any ordinary stick for other purposes, e.g. for punitive <a href=\"/wiki/Caning\" title=\"Caning\">caning</a> (compare <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Rulering&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Rulering (page does not exist)\">rulering</a>).<sup id=\"cite_ref-corpunDlySktch3b_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-corpunDlySktch3b-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Some are <a href=\"/wiki/Telescoping_(mechanics)\" title=\"Telescoping (mechanics)\">telescopic</a> and can be carried in a <a href=\"/wiki/Pocket\" title=\"Pocket\">pocket</a> like a <a href=\"/wiki/Pen\" title=\"Pen\">pen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-telescopic_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-telescopic-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Pointer_(rod)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-dictcom-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-dictcom_1-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/pointer\">\"pointer\"</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/Reference.com\" title=\"Reference.com\">Reference.com</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">23 April</span> 2010</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=pointer&amp;rft.pub=Reference.com&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fdictionary.reference.com%2Fbrowse%2Fpointer&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3APointer+%28rod%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-uiuc-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-uiuc_2-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20100621013851/http://demo.physics.uiuc.edu/LectDemo/scripts/demo_descript.idc?DemoID=1052\">\"UIUC Physics Lecture Demo: Pointer Rod\"</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Illinois_at_Urbana%E2%80%93Champaign\" title=\"University of Illinois at Urbana\u2013Champaign\">University of Illinois at Urbana\u2013Champaign</a>. 1996. Archived from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://demo.physics.uiuc.edu/lectdemo/scripts/demo_descript.idc?DemoID=1052\">the original</a> on 21 June 2010<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">23 April</span> 2010</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=UIUC+Physics+Lecture+Demo%3A+Pointer+Rod&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Illinois+at+Urbana%E2%80%93Champaign&amp;rft.date=1996&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fdemo.physics.uiuc.edu%2Flectdemo%2Fscripts%2Fdemo_descript.idc%3FDemoID%3D1052&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3APointer+%28rod%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-corpunDlySktch3b-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-corpunDlySktch3b_3-0\">^</